This app is almost perfect. [UPDATE] - Wow, I stand corrected.. it IS perfect! After I posted my review below, the developer commented in response to my review and pointed out how I could accomplish what I describe in my review.  SWEET!  :) ------------ [ORIGINAL REVIEW BELOW] The only improvement I would love to see is an option to do circuit weight training instead of the standard - having to complete all of the Reps for a given exercise before you can move on to the next exercise when you are running a routine.  I like to do one set on each exercise I am doing and work through all of the exercises in my routine in succession. In other words, one set on bench press, one set on overhead press, one set on arm extensions, Etc, and then come back to the first exercise and start my second set and work through each of the exercises again in a circuit.  Currently in the app, if you run a routine that you have created, then it assumes you are going to complete all of your sets for a given exercise before you move on to the next one. If the app would provide an option to check mark "circuit training" and change the functionality to allow for this type of routine, that would be awesome
replyContent: Thanks, Michael! You can accomplish this by using the superset feature, so long as each exercise is strength type. Edit your routine and press the superset link icon next to each exercise you want included. Now, when you run your routine, there will be an additional set of arrows at the top of the page that you can navigate the circuit with.

content: Simple to use and just whatI was looking for.

I highly recommend giving this a try if you like tracking your progress and you're currently using a log book, spreadsheets or some other inferior application.

replyContent: Hi David, the csv file can be exported at any time. If you don't have network access at the time of your workout, you can export it after you leave the gym or wherever you are that you don't have service. It's really no different than waiting to plug it into a computer at home to copy a file off your phone.

content: I've used it for about a week and so so good.  I mainly wanted something to keep a list of the exercises I want to do each day and it works better than I expected. I particularly like how easy it is to check the history of each exercise. Well done.

replyContent: Thanks for your feedback Chuck! We're happy to say that we added an option to export to Excel format in a recent release! Make sure your Simple Workout Log is updated to the most recent version and you will find the export option in the slide up menu. Because you are using Pro, the files can be emailed to your Cloud account email address.

content: Used it since the beginning. Excellent way to track progress. 5 stars

replyContent: Thanks for your review, Jesse. I'm glad to say that the app currently supports supersets! To create a superset, build a routine on the routine tab, then use the chain link icons to link the exercises you want to be part of your superset. When you run the routine, arrows show up at the top of the screen to navigate the exercises in your superset.

replyContent: Hello Jack! The easiest way to get all your exercise data on your PC is to export the data via email. Simply start Simple Workout Log, press the "settings gear" in the lower right corner, then press the "Export" button. Next, press the "Email" button. If you have an account already, it will email you the data. If not, you can create a new account.

replyContent: Thanks for the review Matthew! We do currently have a history by day feature. You can access it by going to the History section. At the top of the history window, there is a small drop down menu on the left side that says 'Name' by default. Tap that and select 'Date' then you can choose a specific date to see what exercises you completed that day.

replyContent: Thanks for the great review Jim! You can delete your exercises in the History section, either individual workouts, or entire exercises. Just go to History from the main screen of the app, then select the exercise you want to delete.

replyContent: Hello Jennelle! If you touch the time on the timer, it will open a dialog for you to adjust the count down time. You can also modify categories/routines after they've been saved by going into the Routine section and pressing the gear icon next to the workout you would like to edit. Once there, additional exercises can be added or deleted.
